Walk [[back and forth]].

===Etymology===
Compare {{cog|tbq-pro|*m-p(j)up}}, whence {{cog|bo|འབུབ་པ||turned over or upside down}}, {{cog|tbq-lob-pro|*pup||to turn over; to search for}} (STEDT, {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Within Chinese, cognate with {{och-l|複|id=2|lined (garment); double}}, {{och-l|覆|id=1|to cover}}, {{och-l|覆|id=4|to turn over}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

